<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-10-01T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-10-01T16:00:00-05:00" n="826" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d826">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/7465a: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wallace</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-10-01T17:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">October
                                            1, 1920—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>1526. Press reports that French have threatened their Black Sea fleet
                                will take action against Soviet Russia unless all French prisoners
                                in Russia are repatriated by October 1st and that wireless message
                                from Moscow quotes Chicherin as saying “We bow to brute force”.</p>
                            <pb facs="0785" n="685" xml:id="pg_685"/>
                            <p>Inquire at Foreign Office concerning alleged French threat and cable
                                all possible facts.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>